Ramaphosa made the announcement when he delivered a eulogy on the day of laying to rest a towering figure in South Africa's history. Leaders and ordinary people across the country and the continent united in honouring Madikizela Mandela. While some of the harsh realities of what she suffered were acknowledged, the legacy of the selflessness and fearlessness she represented was also celebrated. Tshepo Ikaneng reports... --SABC--